    "abstract": "CD1a-autoreactive T cells represent a significant proportion of circulating \u03b1\u03b2 T cells in humans and appear to be enriched in the skin. How their autoreactivity is regulated remains unclear. In this issue of JEM, Cotton et al. (2021. J. Exp. Med.https://doi.org/10.1084/jem.20202699) show that CD1a molecules do not randomly survey cellular lipids but instead capture certain lipid classes that broadly interfere with the binding of autoreactive T cell antigen receptors to the target CD1a. These findings provide new potential therapeutic avenues for manipulating CD1a autoreactive T cell responses.",
